# Website Structure Documentation
# tatvadesai.github.io - Personal Website

## Technology Stack
- **Generator**: Jekyll (Ruby-based static site generator)
- **Styling**: Custom CSS with CSS variables (supports light/dark themes)
- **Hosting**: GitHub Pages

## Directory Structure

```
├── _config.yml          # Jekyll configuration
├── _layouts/            # Page layout templates (3 layouts)
├── _essays/             # Essay collection (2 essays)
├── _posts/              # Blog posts organized by date
├── assets/
│   ├── css/             # Stylesheets
│   └── skill-issue/     # Images for skill-issue page
│       ├── shannon.jpeg      # Claude Shannon portrait
│       ├── feynman.jpeg      # Richard Feynman portrait
│       └── dhirubhai.jpeg    # Dhirubhai Ambani portrait
├── cv/                  # CV/Resume section
└── _site/               # Generated static site (auto-built)
```

## Main Pages
- **index.markdown**     → Homepage (/)
- **about.markdown**     → About page (/about/)
- **skill-issue.markdown** → Skill Issue gallery (/skill-issue/)
- **essays.html**        → Essays listing (/essays/)
- **404.html**           → Custom 404 error page

## Key Files
- **Gemfile** / **Gemfile.lock** → Ruby dependencies
- **.gitignore** → Git ignore patterns
- **favicon.ico** → Site favicon

## CSS Variables
Uses CSS custom properties for theming:
- `--text-accent` → Accent text color (gold/amber in dark theme)

## skill-issue Page Structure
A visual gallery page featuring portraits of influential people:
- Grid layout using CSS Grid (auto-fit, min 400px)
- Square aspect ratio images with object-fit: cover
- Gradient overlay with name labels
- Currently features: Claude Shannon, Richard Feynman, Dhirubhai Ambani

## Notes
- Images should be placed in /assets/skill-issue/ 
- Use leading slash for absolute paths in src attributes (e.g., /assets/skill-issue/image.jpeg)
- JPEG format preferred for photographs
